GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Controller prepares the Form 990. The Executive Director does an initial review along with the Board of Directors. The Treasure does a final review on behalf of the Board of Directors and signs the return.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Organization's Board of Directors and the staff are required to review the written conflict of interest policy annually, and indicate by signature that they are compliant with the policy. Copies of signed policies are kept in administrative files.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Executive Director compensation is reviewed and approved annually by the Board of Directors. The Compensation package is determined after a review of comparable non-profit entities located in the Hampton Roads area as well as other Habitat affiliate locations. A market analysis is cmpleted for other highly compensated positions and resulting compensation is approved by the Board of Directors as part of the annual budgeting process.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Governing documents are made available annually to our auditors. The audit report and other governing documents are provided to the public upon request.
